[
    {
        "content": "<p>Splitting this off from:</p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"461444\">Sam Mohr</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/304641-ideas/topic/reflecting.20on.20static.20dispatch/near/493455538\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>We do <code>map</code> and <code>map_err</code>, but <code>map_ok</code> and <code>map_err</code> would make more sense</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 493505713,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1736827019
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I tried this out in the realworld app and it immediately made things clearer. Here's an example:</p>",
        "id": 493505756,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1736827049
    },
    {
        "content": "<h2>Before</h2>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">params</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Request</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">Str</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Str</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">params</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">req</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">path</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">split_first</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s2\">\"?\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">map</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">after</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">with_default</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s2\">\"\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">split_on</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s2\">\"&amp;\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">map</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">param</span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">when</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">param</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">split_first</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s2\">\"=\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"no\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">({</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">before</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">after</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">})</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">before</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">after</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"no\">Err</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">NotFound</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">param</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 493505769,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1736827062
    },
    {
        "content": "<h2>After</h2>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">params</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Request</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">Str</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Str</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">params</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">req</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">path</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">split_first</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s2\">\"?\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">map_ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">after</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">with_default</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s2\">\"\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">split_on</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s2\">\"&amp;\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">map</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">param</span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">when</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">param</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">split_first</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s2\">\"=\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"no\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">({</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">before</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">after</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">})</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">before</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">after</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"no\">Err</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">NotFound</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">param</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 493505774,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1736827070
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>in the first version, there are two <code>.map</code> calls, one to <code>Result.map</code> and the other to <code>List.map</code>, but you have to look at the previous call to notice that <code>split_first</code> returns a <code>Result</code> and <code>split_on</code> returns a <code>List</code></p>",
        "id": 493505896,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1736827128
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>in the second version, every single function call after <code>req.path()</code> is uniquely identifiable without the module name, and <code>req.path()</code> has the variable name to tell you it's a request</p>",
        "id": 493505948,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1736827169
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I guess you don't know for sure that the <code>map</code> at the end is specifically <code>List.map</code>, but at least I can infer from the name that it's a collection (which is the relevant thing; I know it's being called N times instead of 0-1 times) as opposed to a <code>Result</code></p>",
        "id": 493506070,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1736827218
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>if we changed <code>split_first</code> and <code>split_on</code> to return tuples, and also did the <code>.get_0()</code> idea to replace <code>.0</code> accessors, then this could become:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">params</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Request</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">Str</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Str</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">params</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">req</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">path</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">split_first</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s2\">\"?\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">map_ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">get_1</span><span class=\"p\">())</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">with_default</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s2\">\"\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">split_on</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s2\">\"&amp;\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">map</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">param</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">param</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">split_first</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s2\">\"=\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">??</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">param</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"\"</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 493506855,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1736827799
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Might be a bit soon, but I'm happy to make an Issue for this <code>Result.map</code> -&gt; <code>Result.map_ok</code> and start including it in this round of breaking changes.</p>",
        "id": 493510222,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1736830263
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It feels good to break things, right? No need to keep stuff working, makes our job easier</p>",
        "id": 493510277,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736830320
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>works for me!</p>",
        "id": 493511241,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1736830996
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm definitely sold on trying this</p>",
        "id": 493511249,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1736831001
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I’m all for this. The difference to something like mapping a list is that here you’re only mapping data under certain conditions (if it’s <code>Ok</code>), which it’s good for the name to imply. As opposed to a list mapping, where you are mapping the data unconditionally.</p>",
        "id": 493557742,
        "sender_full_name": "Kasper Møller Andersen",
        "timestamp": 1736851845
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>A good explanation!</p>",
        "id": 493557849,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736851887
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Do you also want to change Result.map2 to Result.map2_ok (or similar)?</p>",
        "id": 493689079,
        "sender_full_name": "Chuck Daniels",
        "timestamp": 1736897867
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I feel like we don't want to change that. <code>map2</code> feels fine because we're combining/chaining them. But I'm not sure on that.</p>",
        "id": 493689426,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1736898044
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>map2</code> probably should be renamed to <code>chain</code> or something similar</p>",
        "id": 493689694,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1736898171
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That looks a lot nicer in record builder</p>",
        "id": 493689719,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1736898186
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Though it is less searchable so <span aria-label=\"shrug\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f937\" role=\"img\" title=\"shrug\">:shrug:</span></p>",
        "id": 493689734,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1736898202
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>How about <code>Result.combine</code>? -- I like <code>chain</code> too</p>",
        "id": 493689936,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1736898310
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What I like about <code>chain</code> is I think it tells me more about what it's doing and why I would use it. I feel like <code>map2</code> is less friendly for anyone not already familiar with FP.</p>",
        "id": 493690791,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1736898843
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>A better name might also be some sort of join. Cause it takes 2 results and joins them into 1, but map2 is definitely a traditional name</p>",
        "id": 493692815,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1736900021
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>My concern with <em>naming</em> it something completely different than <code>Result.map_ok</code> would make it appear that it <em>does</em> something completely different when the only difference is that the given mapping function takes 2 args rather than only 1. Further, a name like <code>chain</code> (from my limited exposure to other FP langs/libs) seems more akin to bind/flat_map, but please do correct me if I'm off here.</p>",
        "id": 493695933,
        "sender_full_name": "Chuck Daniels",
        "timestamp": 1736902068
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, chain really only looks good in record builder apis and is not really meaningful elsewhere.</p>",
        "id": 493696191,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1736902246
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Could call that out in the name and just call it <code>Result.build</code></p>",
        "id": 493696462,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1736902411
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>How about <code>Result.lift2</code>?</p>",
        "id": 493702979,
        "sender_full_name": "Chuck Daniels",
        "timestamp": 1736906039
    }
]